# Requirements Analysis
## Johnny Apple Trees Ledger

##1. Problem Statment

Johnny Apple Trees LLC manages rental properties and must track income, expenses, and property information. Currently, much of this information is stored manually across multiple systems, making it difficult to maintain accurate records and quickly evaluate financial performance.

The purpose of Johnny Apple Trees Ledger system is to provide a centralized digital ledger for managing rental property finances. The system will allow property owners to record rent payments, log expenses, track individual properties, and generate clear financial records for business management and tax preparation. 

---

## 2. Functional Requirements

The system must provide the following core functionality:

### Property Management
- Users can create, edit, and delete property records.
- Each property stores information such as address, purchase price, and notes.

### Income Tracking
- Users can record rental income for each property.
- Income records include amount, date received, and description.

### Expense Tracking
- Users can log expenses associated with each property.
- Expenses include cost, date, category (maintenance, utilities, taxes, etc.), and notes.

### Ledger View
- The system will display a chronological ledger of financial transactions.
- Users can filter entries by property or transaction type.

### Financial Summary
- The system will calculate total income, total expenses, and net profit for properties.

---

## 3. Non-Functional Requirements

### Usability
The system should provide a clean and simple interface so property owners can easily enter and review financial data.

### Reliability
The system must store data securely and prevent accidental loss of financial records.

### Maintainability
The codebase should be structured so future features such as reporting tools or tenant management can be added.

### Performance
The system should load property and financial data quickly even when multiple properties and transactions are stored.

---

## 4. Scope

### In Scope
- Property record management
- Rental income tracking
- Expense tracking
- Basic financial summaries
- Web-based user interface

### Out of Scope (Initial Version)
- Automated bank integration
- Tenant portals
- Online rent payment processing
- Tax filing automation

These features may be considered in future versions of the system.

---

## 5. Constraints

The project is being developed as part of a capstone course with limited development time and resources. Additional constraints include:

- Single developer project
- Limited timeline for development
- Must use tools appropriate for student-level development
- Must be hosted and version-controlled using GitHub

---

## 6. Success Criteria

The project will be considered successful if:

- Users can create and manage property records
- Users can record income and expenses
- The system correctly calculates profit and loss
- Financial data can be easily viewed and organized
- The application runs reliably in a web environment
